article.headline: Missouri State 72, Illinois State 61
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Blake Ahearn scored 18 points and connected on four of six 3-pointers Wednesday to lead Missouri State in a 72-61 win over Illinois State. Ahearn was 5-for-10 from the floor for the Bears (19-7, 11-6 Missouri Valley), who shot 55 percent in the first half on their way to a 37-29 halftime lead. Nathan Bilyeu added 13 points with five rebounds and three assists. Roberto Fortes led the way for Illinois State (9-17, 4-13), scoring 14 points with four rebounds off the bench for the Redbirds. Greg Dilligard added 11 points, a game-high nine rebounds and three blocks. But the Redbirds shot only 39 percent from the field in the game, compared to the Bears' 50 percent. Illinois State also had 18 turnovers in the loss. Dale Lamberth and Kellen Easley came off the bench to score 12 points and 10 points, respectively, for Missouri State.
